[2] Saudi Arabia 0 new cases, 0 new fatalities - MOH 21 Jun 2015
Date: 21 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi MOH [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-21-001.aspx


As of 12 noon today, 21 Jun 2015, there have been a total of:
1038 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
459 deaths,
573 recoveries, and
6 currently active cases.

In the past 24 hours there have been:
0 newly confirmed cases,
0 newly reported fatalities,
1 newly reported recovery.

[reported case fatality rate: 44.2 percent]

Information on newly reported recovery:
Aa 46-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker from Riyadh with history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported as a newly confirmed case on 14 Jun 2015, at which time he was noted to be in stable condition. At time of initial confirmation, he denied history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or the community. - Mod.MPP]

